---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.jsx';
import Divider from '../../components/Divider.jsx';
import CardPlaceholder from '../../components/templates/CardPlaceholder';
import ThreeCardReading from "../../components/ThreeCardReading.jsx";

import '../../styles/init.css';

const cardData = await Astro.glob("../../content/markdown/cards/*.md");
const mappedCardData = cardData.map((data) => {
  return {
    frontmatter: data.frontmatter,
    content: data.rawContent(),
  }
})
---

<Layout title='Tiny Visions - Three Card Reading'>
  <Navbar client:load activeLink="readings" />
  <main class='bg-palette-c-dark text-palette-c-light sm:text-2xl flex flex-col items-center'>
    <Divider/>
    <header class='flex flex-col items-center justify-center m-4'>
      <h2 class='text-2xl sm:text-4xl text-center font-bold text-palette-c-accent'>Three Card Reading</h2>
      <p class='md:w-1/2 m-8 sm:text-2xl text-left'>
        With this traditional approach, three tarot cards are drawn, allowing you to interpret their meanings and ties to one another. From left to right, each card represents the past, present, and future.
      </p>
    </header>
    <Divider/>

    <article class='md:w-1/2 flex flex-wrap gap-8 m-12 mb-0 items-around justify-around'>
      <div>
        <CardPlaceholder/>
        <p class='text-center my-6'>PAST</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <CardPlaceholder/>
        <p class='text-center my-6'>PRESENT</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <CardPlaceholder/>
        <p class='text-center my-6'>FUTURE</p>
      </div>
    </article>
    <section class='flex flex-col gap-4 mx-12 mt-4 items-center justify-center'>
      <p class='md:w-1/2'>
        The first card symbolizes the echoes of past events and circumstances which have shaped your present existence. 
        The second card, representing the ever-shifting present, may reveal knowledge and obstacles standing in your way. 
        The third card may unlock the secrets of what has yet to come, providing a glimpse into the path that lies ahead of you. 
        With your interpretation of each card, you may gain a deeper understanding of your situation and potential paths forward.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class='max-w-5xl mx-auto'>
      <ThreeCardReading cards={mappedCardData} client:load />
    </div>

    <Divider/>

    <div class='mb-12'></div>

  </main>
</Layout>